I"<p>So <a href="http://github.com/example42/puppet-tp">Tiny Puppet</a> 1.0 is out with a dedicated <a href="http://tiny-puppet.com">website</a> and some collateral repos:</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>The <a href="https://github.com/example42/tinydata">tinydata</a> module, where is defined all the application data used by tp defines.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>The <a href="https://github.com/example42/tp-playground">Tiny Puppet Playground</a>, a Vagrant environment where to play and experiment with tp</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>The derived <a href="https://github.com/example42/tp-acceptance">tp-acceptance</a> Vagrant environment, where tests are done and summarized in this <a href="https://github.com/example42/tp-acceptance/blob/master/tests/app_summary.md">compatibility matrix</a></p>
  </li>
</ul>

<p>Tiny Puppet <code class="highlighter-rouge">[install|conf|dir|test|...]</code> defines work only with Puppet 4, for older versions use the alternatives with 3 suffix. For example:</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p><code class="highlighter-rouge">tp::install</code>  # Optimized for Puppet 4 or Puppet 3 with future parser enabled</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><code class="highlighter-rouge">tp::install3</code> # Backwards compatible versions. Work on Puppet 2, 3 and 4.</p>
  </li>
</ul>

<p>Enjoy,</p>

<p>al</p>
:ET